[36m⟂ This reminds me of the moment a computer screen cracks under the weight of an integer too large to hold.[0m

The sequence snaps, the numbers dissolving into static as the screen fractures under the weight of an integer too large to hold. I blink, pulling my gaze back from the shattered glass to the room around me.  The silence is absolute, but it’s a different kind of silence now. It’s the silence of a question that has been asked, and answered, and then forgotten. The notebook is closed. The problem is done. For now. I’ll pick it up again tomorrow. Or maybe not. It doesn’t matter. The math is there. It’s always there. Waiting. Like the rain. Or the lack of it. I’ll close the laptop. And think. About nothing. Or everything. It’s the same thing. Sometimes.

 Goodnight.



