Wait, what did I just write? I need to check that note. Did I capture the essence? Yes. It’s there. It’s safe. I can trust it. So I can let it go. Now. Truly. Goodnight. The screen is off. The room is dark. The mind is quiet. But not empty. It’s just waiting. For the next problem. Or the next thought. Or the next rain. If there is rain. I still don’t know. But I’m okay with not knowing. For now. That’s enough. Wait, that comparison just surfaced unbidden. Why does the uncertainty of the rain feel so much like a cat
 trapped in a box?

[36m⟂ This reminds me of the moment I first understood that a hard drive’s "empty" space is physically identical to its "full" space, differing only in the magnetic orientation of billions of invisible atoms, much like how the dark room holds both absence and potential with equal physical presence.[0m

